        "width": 482.7,
        "height": 29.08
      },
      "text": "Ackaert et al. Presented at ASTMH 2021 - Virtual meeting. P582.",
      "style": {
        "font_size_pt": 12.0
      },
      "z": 4,
      "placeholder_id": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "shp65",
      "type": "body",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 497.09,
        "y": 420.29,
        "width": 680.91,
        "height": 161.56
      },
      "text": "No deaths, serious adverse events (AEs) or AEs leading to JNJ-1802 discontinuation.\nNo clinically relevant changes in electrocardiograms, laboratory tests or vital signs.\nTwo grade 2 events of rash occurred, which were considered very likely related to JNJ-1802 by the investigator. These resolved after 35–47 days.",
      "style": {
        "font_size_pt": 14.0
      },
      "z": 5,
      "placeholder_id": null,
